Set Up Messaging for In-App and Web

Understand the four stages of setting up Messaging for In-App and Web. We recommend following them in order for a smooth experience.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience.
 This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels
 This article doesnâ€™t apply to:	Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

USER PERMISSIONS
To set up this feature:	
Customize Application
Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions

Follow the four stages of setup in order:

1. Prepare a Salesforce org
Give agents the right permissions, set up Omni-Channel, create an Omni Flow, add a messaging channel, connect to the Service console, and add user verification.

2. Configure a deployment
Connect your channel with a new web or mobile deployment. Set branding and configure more features.

3. Set up a pre-chat form
Create an optional pre-chat form with standard or custom fields to gather critical details for agents.

4. Add a bot or push notifications
Set up an optional bot or mobile push notifications to supercharge your messaging channel.

Give Users Access to Messaging for In-App and Web
To let agents message with customers, create and assign a permission set for Messaging for In-App and Web agents.
Prepare a Salesforce Org for Messaging for In-App and Web
Build a strong foundation for your new messaging channel. Create a new Salesforce org, set up Omni-Channel and Omni Flow, and add your messaging channel.

Configure a Messaging for Web Deployment
Connect your messaging channel to a website with a new embedded deployment.
Configure a Messaging for In-App Deployment
Connect your messaging channel to a mobile app with a new embedded deployment.
Configure a Custom Client Deployment for Messaging for In-App and Web (Beta)
To enjoy granular control of your web or mobile app messaging experience, create a custom client deployment for Messaging for In-App and Web.

Customize Pre-Chat for Messaging for In-App and Web
Ask customers to fill out visible pre-chat fields before starting a messaging session, or auto-fill hidden pre-chat fields when the conversation begins.
Map Pre-Chat Values in Omni-Channel Flow
Omni Flow sends pre-chat form data to the messaging session for a more informed agent experience.

Preview Your Messaging for Web Setup
After adding Messaging for Web to your site, preview your branding and configurations.
Troubleshoot Messaging for In-App and Web Setup
Respond to error messages you may encounter while setting up Messaging for In-App and Web.
title: Setting Up Messaging for In-App and Web
